# Environment Variables Template for Nanochat Training
#
# INSTRUCTIONS:
#   1. For local development: Copy to .env and fill in actual values
#   2. For Runpod deployment: Set these in Runpod Console → Secrets
#
# NOTE: .env is gitignored to prevent accidental secret commits
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# RUNPOD SECRETS (Encrypted)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# These should be configured as SECRETS in Runpod Console (encrypted storage):

# HuggingFace Token - REQUIRED
# Purpose: Download training data (FineWeb), upload checkpoints to HF Hub
# Permissions: Must have "Write" access
# Get from: https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
HF_TOKEN=hf_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Weights & Biases API Key - RECOMMENDED
# Purpose: Real-time training monitoring dashboards
# Get from: https://wandb.ai/authorize
WANDB_API_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# GitHub Personal Access Token - OPTIONAL
# Purpose: Clone private forks (only needed if your fork is private)
# Scopes: repo (full repository access)
# Get from: https://github.com/settings/tokens
GITHUB_PAT=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# RUNPOD ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (Plain Text)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# These can be set as regular environment variables (not secrets):

# GitHub Username - OPTIONAL
# Purpose: Determines which fork to clone (defaults to 'originalzen')
# Used in: runpod_onstart.sh → git clone https://github.com/${GIT_USERNAME}/nanochat.git
GIT_USERNAME=xxxxxxxxxxxx

# Weights & Biases Run Name - OPTIONAL
# Purpose: Name shown in W&B dashboard for this training run
# Example values: "d20", "my_first_run", "experiment_001"
WANDB_RUN=d20

# Git Commit Author Name - OPTIONAL
# Purpose: Git commit metadata (only if making commits on Runpod)
GIT_USER_NAME=Your Full Name

# Git Commit Author Email - OPTIONAL
# Purpose: Git commit metadata (only if making commits on Runpod)
GIT_USER_EMAIL=your.email@example.com

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ADVANCED (Usually don't need to change)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Nanochat Base Directory - OPTIONAL
# Purpose: Where checkpoints, data, and reports are cached
# Default: $HOME/.cache/nanochat
# NANOCHAT_BASE_DIR=/custom/path/to/cache

# Number of GPUs - OPTIONAL
# Purpose: Override automatic GPU detection
# Default: Auto-detected via nvidia-smi
# NPROC_PER_NODE=8

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECURITY NOTES
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# CRITICAL:
#   - Never commit .env to git (already in .gitignore)
#   - Never share HF_TOKEN, WANDB_API_KEY, or GITHUB_PAT publicly
#   - Use Runpod Secrets (not environment variables) for API keys and tokens
#
# TOKEN PERMISSIONS:
#   - HF_TOKEN: Must have "Write" permission (not just "Read")
#   - GITHUB_PAT: Needs "repo" scope (only required for private forks)
#
# ROTATION:
#   - If any token is exposed, rotate immediately on respective platform
#   - Runpod Secrets can be updated without redeploying pods
#
